                           <font color="green"> <h1> Our Mission </h1>
                            <h3><font color="green">Hoedspruit Farming  Services</font> </h3>



                            <p>The Hoedspruit Farming Services segment comprises the Grain Management and Retail and Equipment divisions. These divisions serve the primary agricultural production sector with a specific focus on the maize value chain (from land preparation, seeds and other inputs, harvesting, grain procurement and secure storage), but also address the needs of producers of wheat, soya and sunflower. </p>

                            <h4><font color="green">Retail and Equipment  </font></h4>

                            <p>A comprehensive range of products and services is available through a
                                network of retail outlets in both urban and rural areas. The Retail and Equipment division
                                provides farmers with the primary inputs and mechanisation solutions necessary for a successful crop.
                                The AFGRI brands associated with this division include: Town&Country; FarmCity; and Partrite.
                                As an authorised John Deere dealer AFGRI is able to provide a one-stop mechanisation solution to
                                farmers of all sizes.
                                The results of the Australian and Zambian subsidiaries and our other activities in Africa are
                                consolidated with the Retail and Equipment division. </p>

                            <h4><font color="green">Grain Management </font></h4>

                            <p>The combination of world-class technology in silo inventory management,
                                electronic silo certificates and a wealth of experience in grain procurement,
                                handling and collateral management, positions AFGRI as an industry leader in the handling 
                                and storage of grains. AFGRI Grain Management offers secure storage of agricultural products
                                throughout Southern Africa. Grain is handled and stored separately according to its characteristics 
                                and the division provides both quality and quantity guarantees.
                                Besides its owned infrastructure in South Africa, the division manages various storage locations 
                                in South and Southern Africa, provides collateral management services to financiers and offers grain 
                                procurement services. 
                            </p>
                            <h4><font color="green">Hoedspruit Farming Financial Services </font></h4>
                            <p> The Group's Financial Services segment comprises three distinct operating units:
                                GroCapital Financial Services provides specialised finance to businesses involved in the agricultural
                                value chain. A wide range of products, services, skills and expertise are available to customers in 
                                various other sectors of the economy. Product development is a vital element to the success of this 
                                unit. The specialised finance department supplies tailormade financial solutions to the secondary
                                agricultural and related industries with a focus on emerging markets and an emphasis on Africa.
                                UNIGRO Financial Services (formerly AFGRI Capital) cultivates personal, long-term relationships with 
                                farmers and has a thorough understanding of the agricultural cycle. The business unit acts as an 
                                originator and administrator for the Land and Agricultural Development Bank of South Africa 
                                (Land Bank) in the extension of agricultural credit in the form of short, medium or long-term 
                                facilities to primary producers of agricultural products.

                                UNIGRO Insurance provides risk solutions and insurance. It is a composite insurance broker 
                                specialising in all aspects of short-term and long-term insurance such as personal lines insurance,
                                business insurance, farming insurance, crop insurance, partnership assurance, investments, financial 
                                planning, life insurance, credit life insurance, healthcare/medical aid, estate planning and all 
                                agri-related risks. 
                            </p>
                            <h4><font color="green">Hoedspruit Farming Foods <font></h4>
                            <p>The segment is comprised of two divisions: Animal Protein and Oil, Milling and Protein. </p>

                            <h4><font color="green">Animal Protein </font></h4>

                            <p>Animal Protein comprises AFGRI’s integrated poultry operation and the Group’s animal feed factories.
                                AFGRI Animal Feeds plays a vital role in converting raw grain, together with other key elements of protein and energy, into balanced feed for the livestock and dairy industries. In particular approximately 19% of AFGRI Animal Feeds’ production is utilised by AFGRI Poultry as specially formulated high performance rations.

                                AFGRI Poultry produces broiler day-old chicks at its hatchery facility. It then grows and processes
                                broilers into frozen whole birds and individually quick-frozen (IQF) portions. While most of the 
                                product consists of IQF portions, fresh and frozen whole birds and by-products are also sold to the retail chains and independent wholesalers. During 2012, AFGRI Poultry was also appointed a supplier of poultry products to YUM (KFC).

                                AFGRI Poultry’s products are retailed under the Daybreak Superior brand as well as supermarket house
                                brands.

                                The Animal Protein division also accommodates the Group’s supplier of laboratory and scientific analyt
                                cal equipment, LabWorld. Agencies have been specifically selected based on technical competence and 
                                quality and include Skalar, Perten, Chopin, Gerhardt, PS Analytical and Ankom. 
                            </p>
                            <h4 ><font color="green">Oil, Milling and Protein</font> </h4>

                            <p>Nedan has cotton, sunflower and soybean crushing and oil extraction plants, and processes oil and 
                                other raw materials into edible oils, fats and high-protein textured vegetable products for the food 
                                processing and animal feeds industries. It is the market leader in texturized soya protein for human 
                                consumption and oil cakes for the animal feed industry.

                                AFGRI Milling comprises three yellow maize mills acquired during 2011 and which have been included
                                in the Group's results from 1 December 2011. The mills produce yellow maize grits which are used in
                                the production of various maize based value-added products such as cereals, crisps and thickeners.</p></font>
                           
